ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: ASEC Symptom code
Notes: 1 = Dry mouth; 2 = Drowsiness; 3 = Insomnia; 4 = Blurred vision; 5 = Headache; 6 = Constipation; 7 = Diarrhea; 8 = Increased appetite; 9 = Decreased appetite; 10 = Nausea or vomiting; 11 = Problems with urination; 12 = Problems with sexual function; 13 = Palpitations; 14 = Feeling light-headed on standing; 15 = Feeling like the room is spinning; 16 = Sweating; 17 = Increased body temperature; 18 = Tremor; 19 = Disorientation; 20 = Yawning; 21 = Weight gain

ElementDescription: ASEC Severity rating
Notes: 0 = Absent; 1 = Mild (or slight nausea); 2 = Moderate (or more nausea); 3 = Severe (or nausea with vomiting)

ElementDescription: ASEC Linked to antidepressant?
What other symptoms have you had since the antidepressant medication (or since last completing the ASEC) that you think may be side-effects of the medication?
Miscellaneous Comments
Have you had any treatment for a side-effect?
Has any side-effect led to you discontinuing the antidepressant medication?
